From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 19:25:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] misc: send SOF between Fruit Jam usbhost control stages

TinyUSB's PIO-USB host runs transfers from a 1 kHz frame timer, so the next
control stage normally follows a real SOF rather than a silent sleep.  The
Linux bridge's skip-ACK probes were waiting about one millisecond without
sending SOF before the IN/status stage.

Send one SOF frame between skip-ACK SETUP and the following control stage.  This
keeps these probes closer to the working TinyUSB/Pico-PIO-USB enumeration
timing.
---
 drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c | 10 ++++++----
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
--- a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
@@ -2784,8 +2784,9 @@ static int fj_usbhost_pio_get_device8_combo_skipack(struct fruitjam_usbhost *uh)
 	scnprintf(uh->last_probe_summary, sizeof(uh->last_probe_summary),
 		  "combo-dma-skipack setup-tx-len=%u", encoded_len);
 
-	usleep_range(FJ_USBHOST_SETUP_ACK_SKIP_DELAY_US,
-		     FJ_USBHOST_SETUP_ACK_SKIP_DELAY_US + 100u);
+	ret = fj_usbhost_pio_sof_burst(uh, 1);
+	if (ret)
+		return ret;
 
 	fj_usbhost_pio_prepare_receive_after_tx(uh);
 	ret = fj_usbhost_pio_send_token(uh, FJ_USB_PID_IN, 0, 0, &encoded_len);
@@ -3545,8 +3546,9 @@ static int fj_usbhost_pio_hub_set_address_skipack(struct fruitjam_usbhost *uh,
 		  "hub-set-address-skipack setup-tx-len=%u sof-frames=%u",
 		  encoded_len, sof_frames);
 
-	usleep_range(FJ_USBHOST_SETUP_ACK_SKIP_DELAY_US,
-		     FJ_USBHOST_SETUP_ACK_SKIP_DELAY_US + 100u);
+	ret = fj_usbhost_pio_sof_burst(uh, 1);
+	if (ret)
+		return ret;
 	ret = fj_usbhost_pio_control_status_in(uh, 0);
 	if (!ret)
 		scnprintf(uh->last_probe_summary,
-- 
